						<summary>

						<p>Slab paved on the floor in the <hi rend="italic">mukhamaṇḍapa</hi> of the Chennakēśava temple.</p>						

						<p>Krōdhi, Māgha, ba. 13, Monday.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in the cyclic year Śukla, Śrāvaṇa ba. 7. On the basis of palaeography it may be assigned to 17th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>It records that Pattikoṇḍa Varadarāja excavated a tank for the merit of Nandyāla Nāraparāju.</p>						

						</summary>
